        (40, 'Dairy', 'Which cheese was first made by French Trappist monks in the early 19th century and named after the abbey?', 'Camembert', 'Port-Salut', 'Reblochon', NULL, 'B', NULL),
        (40, 'Dairy', 'Ricotta cheese is made with which of the following?', 'The Solids Of The Milk', 'The Whey Of The Milk', 'Both The Whey And Solids Of The Milk', NULL, 'B', 'In contrast, most cheese is made from the solids of the milk. '),
        (40, 'Dairy', 'Which of the following cheeses is from Quebec?', 'Mimolette', 'Neufchâtel', 'Riopelle', NULL, 'C', 'Le Riopelle de l \'isle is a triple-cream cheese named after the renowned Quebec painter Jean-Paul Riopelle. It has a buttery taste with hints of mushrooms and hazelnuts.'),
        (40, 'Dairy', 'Which of the following cheeses is often used as a substitute for Parmigiano?', 'Friulano', 'Ricotta', 'Romano', NULL, 'C', 'This hard cheese has a texture very similar to that of Parmigiano and is ideal for grating. '),
        (40, 'Dairy', 'A round soft cheese made from ewe\'s milk and ripened in cabbage leaves is', 'Cotswold', 'Finslaydale', 'Slipcote', NULL, 'C', 'This is one of the oldest (dating to Shakespeare\'s time) and best English cream cheeses. '),
        (40, 'Dairy', 'In what US state is Tillamook cheese made?', 'Minnesota', 'Oregon', 'Wisconsin', NULL, 'B', 'This cheddar cheese gets its name from the town of Tillamook, which is located on the southeast end of Tillamook Bay, on the Pacific Ocean. '),
        (40, 'Dairy', 'What is Yarg?', 'A Cheese', 'Beer And Whiskey', 'A Porridge ', NULL, 'A', 'Yarg is a hard cow\'s milk cheese from Cornwall. Before being left to mature, it is wrapped in nettle leaves to form an edible mouldy rind. The odd name is the family name of its makers, Gray, spelled backward. '),
        (40, 'Desserts', 'What is ambrosia?', 'A Fruity Dessert', 'A Late-Harvest Dessert Wine', 'An Orange-Flavored Liqueur', NULL, 'A', 'Ambrosia usually consists of oranges and bananas mixed with coconut. In Greek mythology, ambrosia was the food of the gods.'),
        (40, 'Desserts', 'A dessert made from milk or cream, sugar, vanilla and cornstarch or gelatin is best described as', 'Blancmange', 'Charlotte', 'Peruvian Cream', NULL, 'A', 'A blancmange is a cooked pudding that is served chilled with a sauce or fruit. Blancmange is one of the oldest desserts and dates back to the Middle Ages.'),
        (40, 'Desserts', 'What does the word "cannoli" refer to?', 'Beans', 'A Dessert', 'A Shape Of Pasta', NULL, 'B', 'Cannoli are deep-fried pastry shells filled with whipped ricotta cheese or cream, chocolate, candied citron and sometimes nuts. '),
        (40, 'Desserts', 'What is congee?', 'Gelatinous Dessert', 'Rice Pudding', 'Type Of Eel', NULL, 'B', 'Boil rice long enough and you will get congee. '),
        (40, 'Desserts', 'Crêpes Suzette includes a sauce made from butter, sugar and which fruit?', 'Banana', 'Lemon', 'Orange', NULL, 'C', 'Orange juice and orange-based liqueur are essential ingredients in crêpes Suzette. '),
        (40, 'Desserts', 'What is a fiadone?', 'Fruit Tart', 'Liqueur', 'Sponge Cake', NULL, 'C', 'Fiadone is made of cream cheese, eggs, flour, lemon peel and Corsican liqueur. It was one of Napoleon\'s favorite desserts.'),
        (40, 'Desserts', 'A dessert of puréed sweetened fruit with custard or whipped cream is called a', 'Fantasy', 'Fool', 'Frippery', NULL, 'B', 'The name "fool" is thought to derive from the French word "fouler," which means "to trample. '),
        (40, 'Desserts', 'Ganache is made with cream and what other ingredient?', 'Almond Paste', 'Chocolate', 'Vanilla', NULL, 'B', 'Ganache is used as an icing on cakes and tortes. '),
        (40, 'Desserts', 'Which of the following nuts is used in the dessert mont-blanc?', 'Almond', 'Chestnut', 'Hazelnut', NULL, 'B', 'Mont-blanc consists of sweetened, vanilla-flavored puréed chestnuts topped with whipped cream. '),
        (40, 'Desserts', 'Struffoli refers to a Neapolitan speciality of small deep fried rounds of dough covered in which of the following?', 'Chocolate', 'Honey', 'Icing Sugar', NULL, 'B', 'Also known as honey balls, struffoli are crunchy on the outside and light on the inside. They are traditionally served at Christmas and Easter and are best served warm.'),
        (40, 'Desserts', 'What is tapioca made from?', 'Cassava', 'Coconut', 'Rice', NULL, 'A', 'Tapioca is derived from the root of the cassava plant. It is used mainly as a thickener.'),
        (40, 'Desserts', 'Which of the following is traditionally used to make zabaglione?', 'Cinzano', 'Port', 'Marsala', NULL, 'C', 'Zabaglione is a foamy Italian dessert. It is made by whisking egg whites, sugar and some kind of alcoholic liquid (for example, white wine, port, or liqueur) together over low heat.'),
        (40, 'fruit', 'What does the word "bing" refer to?', 'Cherries', 'Peaches', 'Plums', NULL, 'A', 'Bing cherries are large, juicy and dark-skinned. '),
        (40, 'Fruit', 'Which green-skinned fruit tastes like a combination of mango, strawberry and pineapple, and is known as a custard apple?', 'Cherimoya', 'Persimmon', 'Pomegranate', NULL, 'A', 'This fruit, native to the Andean highlands of Ecuador and Peru, is oval and has a leathery green skin. Mark Twain called it "the most delicious fruit known to man.'),
        (40, 'Fruit', 'Copra refers to which of the following?', 'Apricot Purée', 'Brazil Nut Oil', 'Coconut Meat', NULL, 'C', 'Copra is the dried meat of the coconut; when pressed, it yields coconut oil. '),
        (40, 'Fruit', 'What is the only tree whose flower is edible?', 'Date', 'Fig', 'Olive', NULL, 'B', NULL),
        (40, 'Fruit', 'In the Middle East, the "poor man\'s food" is', 'Dates', 'Figs', 'Plums', NULL, 'B', NULL),
        (40, 'Fruit', 'In what country did Granny Smith apples originate?', 'Britain', 'New Zealand', 'Usa', NULL, 'B', NULL),
        (40, 'Fruit', 'What other berry do huckleberries resemble?', 'Blackberries', 'Blueberries', 'Raspberries', NULL, 'B', 'Huckleberries range in color from bright red to dark purple to shades of blue. The huckleberry is the state fruit of Idaho.'),
        (40, 'Fruit', 'What country is the fruit jaffa from?', 'Algeria', 'Israel', 'Morocco', NULL, 'B', 'Jaffa is a sweet and almost seedless orange. '),
        (40, 'Fruit', 'Jujube is a Chinese tree that bears fruit about the same size as which of the following?', 'Apple', 'Grapefruit', 'Olive', NULL, 'C', 'Fresh or dried, jujubes can be eaten plain or cooked and can be used like dates. The outside of the fruit is red; the inside is yellowish or green.'),
        (40, 'Fruit', 'Chinese gooseberry is more commonly known as ', 'Cherimoya', 'Kiwi', 'Kumquat', NULL, 'B', 'A Chinese gooseberry resembles a large brown egg with a hairy exterior; it has green flesh and contains edible black seeds. '),
        (40, 'Fruit', 'Kiwano, nispero and mamey sapote are all varieties of', 'Fruit', 'Peppers', 'Squash', NULL, 'A', 'Kiwano is also known as a horned melon because of its spiky exterior. Nispero is a yellowish pear-shaped fruit from the medlar tree. Mamey sapote is a fruit from Mexico and the Caribbean; it has a brown, fuzzy exterior and creamy sweet flesh. '),
        (40, 'Fruit', 'Where did the lemon originate?', 'Central America', 'India', 'Southeast Asia', NULL, 'C', 'Lemons are now grown in tropical and temperate climates around the world. '),
        (40, 'Fruit', 'By weight, approximately what percentage of juice does a lemon contain?', '30 To 45 Per Cent', '50 To 60 Per Cent', '70 To 80 Per Cent', NULL, 'A', NULL),
        (40, 'Fruit', 'Quebec produces approximately how much of the world\'s maple syrup?', '60 Per Cent', '80 Per Cent', '95 Per Cent', NULL, 'B', NULL),
        (40, 'Fruit', 'Angelino, Kelsey and Roysum are all types of', 'Cherries', 'Pears', 'Plums', NULL, 'C', NULL),
        (40, 'Fruit', 'Grapefruit is an ancestor of which fruit?', 'Chermoya', 'Kumquat', 'Pomelo', NULL, 'C', 'The pomelo is the largest of the citrus fruits. It can range from the size of a canteloupe to that of a watermelon.'),
        (40, 'Fruit', 'What kind of flavor does tamarind contribute to a dish?', 'Acidic', 'Salty', 'Sweet', NULL, 'A', 'Tamarind is the fruit of a leguminous evergreen tree that grows in the West Indies, tropical Africa, southeast Asia and India. It is used primarily in the preparation of jams and chutneys.'),
        (40, 'fruit', 'Turnips are particularly high in which vitamin?', 'A', 'B', 'C', NULL, 'C', NULL),
        (40, 'Fruit', 'What is the most widely grown juice orange in the world?', 'Navel', 'Seville', 'Valencia', NULL, 'C', NULL),
        (40, 'Fruit', 'Yuzu is which of the following?', 'Candy', 'Fruit', 'Liqueur', NULL, 'B', 'A yuzu is a Japanese citrus fruit used almost exclusively for its aromatic rind. '),
        (40, 'Grains', 'What does the Hindi word "basmati" mean?', 'Exotic', 'Fragrant', 'Heavenly', NULL, 'B', 'Basmati rice emits a sweet almost nutty fragrance when cooked. '),
        (40, 'Grains', 'Which of the following is NOT a variety of grain?', 'Basmati', 'Kamut', 'Quinoa', NULL, 'A', 'Basmati is a variety of long-grained rice. '),
        (40, 'Grains', 'Bulgur is made from which of the following?', 'Barley', 'Oats', 'Wheat', NULL, 'C', 'Bulgur (sometimes spelled burghul) is a treated whole-wheat grain that is made by cooking wheat then drying and cracking it. '),
        (40, 'Grains', 'From what area of the world does couscous come?', 'Caribbean', 'North Africa', 'Southeast Asia', NULL, 'B', 'Couscous is granular semolina wheat that is cooked and served in both sweet and savory dishes. '),
        (40, 'Grains', 'Groats are associated with which of the following?', 'Beans', 'Grains', 'Nuts', NULL, 'B', 'Groats are what is left of grain kernels after the husks are removed. In the case of wheat, one refers to "berries" instead of groats.'),
        (40, 'Grains', 'Kamut is a variety of which of the following?', 'Bean', 'Rice', 'Wheat', NULL, 'C', 'Kamut is a high-protein wheat that has never been hybridized. '),
        (40, 'Grains', 'What is kasha made of?', 'Barley', 'Buckwheat', 'Wild Rice', NULL, 'B', 'To produce kasha, buckwheat kernels are hulled then crushed. '),
        (40, 'Grains', 'In India, ragi flour is made with', 'Corn', 'Millet', 'Wheat', NULL, 'B', 'Ragi flour gives pancakes a crispness that is not possible with wheat flour. '),
        (40, 'Grains', 'What is spelt?', 'Fish', 'Grain', 'Young Lamb', NULL, 'B', 'Spelt is an ancient variety of wheat consisting of small brown grains; it has a distinctive nutty flavor unlike that of common wheat. '),
        (40, 'Herbs/Spices', 'Cayenne is indigenous to which part of the world?', 'India', 'North Africa', 'South America', NULL, 'C', 'French Guyana to be specific, though the bulk of the world\'s production is now in other areas. '),
        (40, 'Herbs/Spices', 'Coriander is also known as', 'Chervil', 'Cilantro', 'Escarole', NULL, 'B', 'Coriander is also sometimes called Chinese parsley. '),
        (40, 'Herbs/Spices', 'Which of the following is NOT one of the spices in Chinese five-spice powder?', 'Cinnamon', 'Fennel', 'Nutmeg', NULL, 'C', 'Cloves, star anise and Szechuan peppercorn make up the rest of the spices in this pungent mixture of ground spices. '),
        (40, 'Herbs/Spices', 'Which of the following has leaves with a hot, peppery taste?', 'Borage', 'Dandelion', 'Nasturtium', NULL, 'C', 'All parts of the nasturtium plant can be eaten except the roots. '),
        (40, 'Herbs/Spices', 'The spice paprika is most associated with which country\'s cuisine?', 'Hungary', 'Poland', 'Russia', NULL, 'A', 'Paprika, the national spice of Hungary, comes in several varieties, from sweet to hot. '),
        (40, 'Herbs/Spices', 'What color does saffron impart to food?', 'Orange', 'Red', 'Yellow', NULL, 'C', NULL),
        (40, 'Herbs/Spices', 'What herb has an aroma and flavor reminiscent of thyme and mint', 'Oregano', 'Rosemary', 'Savory', NULL, 'C', 'There are two types of savory: summer and winter. The name comes from a Latin word ("satureia") meaning "satyr\'s herb," a reference to the aphrodisiac qualities once attributed to it.'),
        (40, 'History', 'Until the early 1800s which of the following fruits was kapu (forbidden) for the women of Hawaii to eat, under penalty of death?', 'Bananas', 'Kiwis', 'Pineapple', NULL, 'A', 'Bananas were kapu to women because of their phallic shape. Also kapu were coconuts and pork.'),
        (40, 'Meat', 'What are chipolatas?', 'Fried Seasoned Tortilla Chips', 'Small Sausages', 'Very Hot Peppers', NULL, 'B', 'Chipolatas can be made with beef, chicken, or pork, and grilled or fried. The name comes from the Italian word "cipolla," which means "onion.'),
        (40, 'Meat', 'Most commercial gelatins are made from which of the following?', 'Beef', 'Pork', 'Veal', NULL, 'B', 'However, the purest gelatin with the most delicate and richest flavor is obtained from calves\' feet. '),
        (40, 'Meat', 'A New York steak is also known as', 'Porterhouse', 'Rib Eye', 'Striploin', NULL, 'C', NULL),
        (40, 'Meat', 'Which of the following is NOT a traditional pairing with Italian prosciutto?', 'Apple', 'Figs', 'Melon', NULL, 'A', 'The figs and melons are a great complement to the saltiness of the meat. '),
        (40, 'Meat', 'Rilletes is similar to', 'Bacon', 'Pâté', 'Sausage', NULL, 'B', 'Rillettes is a preparation of pork, goose, rabbit or poultry meat that is cooked in lard then pounded into a smooth paste. The mixture is then potted and served as a cold hors d\'oeuvre.'),
        (40, 'Meat', 'The Cajun specialty tasso is a type of', 'Chicken', 'Fish', 'Ham', NULL, 'C', 'Tasso is usually included in jambalaya and is often used in pastas, soups and gravies. '),
        (40, 'Meat', 'What type of ham is smoked over burning juniper bushes?', 'Mangalica', 'Virginia', 'Westphalian', NULL, 'C', NULL),
        (40, 'Misc.', 'In the United States dairy products comprise what percentage of all food consumed?', '29 Per Cent', '35 Per Cent', '42 Per Cent', NULL, 'A', NULL),
        (40, 'Misc.', 'Which of the following foods was Eleanor Roosevelt reputed to have eaten every morning?', 'Chocolate-Covered Garlic', 'Headcheese', 'Rhubarb And Honey', NULL, 'A', 'Her doctor reputedly told her that it would improve her memory. '),
        (40, 'Misc.', 'In the Michelin system for judging restaurants, the highest rating is', 'Three Stars', 'Four Stars', 'Five Stars', NULL, 'A', NULL),
        (40, 'Misc.', 'According to the 2008 Michelin Guide, what city has the most restaurants?', 'New York', 'Paris', 'Tokyo', NULL, 'C', 'Paris had 20,000 and New York 23,000. '),
        (40, 'Misc.', 'Which of the following foods is NOT a good source of Vitamin D?', 'Eggs', 'Oranges', 'Sardines', NULL, 'B', NULL),
        (40, 'Nuts', 'Which of the following nuts contains the most fiber?', 'Almonds', 'Pistachios', 'Walnuts', NULL, 'A', 'Almonds also contain more calcium than any other nut. '),
        (40, 'Nuts', 'Almonds do NOT contain which of the following?', 'Fat', 'Protein', 'Starch', NULL, 'C', NULL),
        (40, 'Nuts', 'Cobnuts is another name for', 'Hazelnuts', 'Peanuts', 'Walnuts', NULL, 'A', 'Hazelnuts are also known as filberts. They are so named because they ripen about the time of St. Philibert\'s Day (August 20). '),
        (40, 'Nuts', 'The macadamia nut is native to which of the following?', 'Australia', 'Hawaii', 'Turkey ', NULL, 'A', 'Also known as a Queensland nut, the macadamia is used in curries and stews in Asia. It is now cultivated extensively in Hawaii and California.'),
        (40, 'Nuts', 'Which is NOT a true nut?', 'Peanut', 'Macadamia', 'Walnut', NULL, 'A', 'The peanut is an underground legume (also called a groundnut or a goober). '),
        (40, 'Nuts', 'Runner, Spanish and Virginia are all names of varieties of ', 'Beans', 'Peanuts', 'Squash', NULL, 'B', NULL),
        (40, 'Nuts', 'China is the world\'s leading peanut producer. The second is', 'India', 'Indonesia', 'The Usa', NULL, 'A', 'The USA is third. '),
        (40, 'Nuts', 'Which nut has the highest fat content?', 'Pecan', 'Pistachio', 'Walnut?', NULL, 'A', 'Pecans are over 70 per cent fat; walnuts 65 per cent; pistachios between 50 and 55 per cent. '),
        (40, 'Oils', 'Balsamic vinegar is made from which of the following grapes?', 'Muscat', 'Pinot Grigio', 'Trebbiano', NULL, 'C', 'Balsamic vinegar is aged in barrels the same way wine is. The older the vinegar, the more intense the taste and the higher the price.'),
        (40, 'Oils', 'Which Italian city is associated with balsamic vinegar?', 'Florence', 'Modena', 'Turin', NULL, 'B', 'Balsamic vinegar has been made in Modena since the Middle Ages. '),
        (40, 'Oils', 'What percentage of the world\'s olive oil is produced in Spain?', '35 Per Cent', '50 Per Cent', '75 Per Cent', NULL, 'C', NULL),
        (40, 'Oils', 'Which of the following oils contains saturated fats?', 'Canola', 'Coconut', 'Olive', NULL, 'B', 'It is rare for a non-animal product to contain saturated fat. Nevertheless, the coconut has been the primary source of fat in the diets of millions of people in the tropical world for generations.'),
        (40, 'Pasta', 'Calzone is a stuffed pizza. What does the word "calzone" mean in Italian?', 'A Lady\'S Purse', 'Shopping Bag', 'Trouser Leg', NULL, 'C', 'But be careful—in Central and South America "calzones" are girls\' underpants. '),
        (40, 'Pasta', 'Cappelletti pasta are similar in shape to what other pasta?', 'Penne', 'Ravioli', 'Rotini', NULL, 'B', 'The word "cappelletti" means "little hats" in Italian. '),
        (40, 'Pasta', 'Which of the following pastas is shaped like a bowtie?', 'Ditalini', 'Farfalle', 'Mostaccioli', NULL, 'B', NULL),
        (40, 'Pasta', 'Which of the following English translations of Italian words is incorrect?', 'Capelli: Hair', 'Linguine: Little Tongues', 'Ravioli: Little Pillows', NULL, 'C', 'This word means "little turnips" in Italian. '),
        (40, 'Processed Foods', 'Self-rising flour is a blend of all-purpose flour, salt and which of the following?', 'Baking Powder', 'Baking Soda', 'Yeast', NULL, 'A', NULL),
        (40, 'Recipes', 'À la Marengo refers to veal or chicken prepared with which of the following?', 'Bacon', 'Cream And Saffron', 'Olive Oil And Garlic', NULL, 'C', 'To prepare a dish à la Marengo, the cook first sautés meat, then braises it with tomatoes, onions, garlic and white wine. '),
        (40, 'Recipes', 'What ingredient is a must in dishes prepared à la périgourdine?', 'Brandy', 'Saffron', 'Truffles', NULL, 'C', NULL),
        (40, 'Recipes', 'A cornmeal and whole wheat dumpling popular in Ghana and used in stews is called', 'Abaloo', 'Agidi', 'Akebia', NULL, 'A', 'Akebia is an Asian fruit; agidi is a Nigerian porridge made with corn starch. '),
        (40, 'Recipes', 'Bourride is a classic fish soup from Provence. Which of the following is a key ingredient?', 'Aïoli', 'Mustard', 'Shallots', NULL, 'A', 'Aïoli is a garlic mayonnaise that also thickens the soup. '),
        (40, 'Recipes', 'Bubble and squeak is an English dish of potato and which of the following?', 'Bacon', 'Cabbage', 'Sausage', NULL, 'B', 'The name is said to come from the sounds the potato–cabbage mixture makes as it cooks. '),
        (40, 'Recipes', 'Cassoulet is a dish from', 'Belgium', 'Canada', 'France', NULL, 'C', NULL),
        (40, 'Recipes', 'What is ceviche (sometimes spelled seviche)?', 'A Poached Shrimp Dish', 'Grilled Beef Kebabs', 'Marinated Raw Fish', NULL, 'C', 'Ceviche consists of fresh fish or shellfish marinated in lemon or lime juice, herbs and aromatic vegetables. '),
        (40, 'Recipes', 'Which of the following vegetables is used in dishes à la Crécy?', 'Carrots', 'Celery', 'Watercress', NULL, 'A', 'Crécy is an area in France that produces fine carrots. '),
        (40, 'Recipes', 'A croque-monsieur is a', 'Chef\'S Hat', 'French Short Order Cook', 'Ham And Cheese Sandwich', NULL, 'C', 'Croque-monsieur is dipped in beaten egg and sautéed in butter, sometimes on a special grilling iron. Gruyère is the traditional cheese used in a croque-monsieur.'),
        (40, 'Recipes', 'To make custard, a cook blends sugar, milk and what other ingredient?', 'Butter', 'Egg Yolks', 'Flour', NULL, 'B', 'Making custard requires gentle heat and slow cooking to prevent curdling. '),
        (40, 'Recipes', 'Which of the following could be used in making the Indian dish dal?', 'Coconut', 'Lentils', 'Rice', NULL, 'B', 'A variety of pulses, such as lentils, beans, peas or chickpeas, can be used to make this thick and spicy dish. '),
        (40, 'Recipes', 'In French cuisine, what is a daube?', 'Beef Dish', 'Dessert', 'Soup', NULL, 'A', 'A daube is made with red wine, vegetables and seasonings, and is braised for several hours. '),
        (40, 'Recipes', 'Feijoada is a Brazilian', 'Meat Kebab', 'Pastry', 'Stew', NULL, 'C', 'This spicy dish is made with beef and includes red or black beans. It is usually served with rice and green cabbage.'),
        (40, 'Recipes', 'Which of the following is the essential ingredient of jambalaya?', 'Lamb', 'Turnips', 'Rice', NULL, 'C', 'Other ingredients can include tomatoes, onions, green peppers, and almost any kind of meat, poultry or seafood. '),
        (40, 'Recipes', 'Kimchi is a spicy Korean dish usually made with', 'Beans', 'Chinese Cabbage', 'Seaweed', NULL, 'B', 'Various seasonings are added to this fermented dish, which is always present at Korean tables. '),
        (40, 'Recipes', 'Fish that has been seasoned, lightly floured, sautéed in butter and served with lemon-flavored butter is prepared in what style?', 'Chasseur', 'Meunière', 'Normande', NULL, 'B', 'This type of preparation can be used with any kind of fish. The dish is always lightly floured, and this provides the name of the dish—"meunière" is French for "a female miller.'),
        (40, 'Recipes', 'Which meat is used in moo shu (or moo shoo) dishes?', 'Beef', 'Chicken', 'Pork', NULL, 'C', 'Scallions and eggs are also often included in this Northern Chinese dish. '),
        (40, 'Recipes', 'What meat is usually used in mulligatawny?', 'Beef', 'Chicken', 'Lamb', NULL, 'B', 'Originally from India, this highly seasoned spicy soup was adopted by the British and is particularly popular in Australia. '),
        (40, 'Recipes', 'The famous Quebec dish poutine does NOT usually include', 'Cheese', 'Gravy', 'Tomatoes', NULL, 'C', 'Poutine consists of french fries topped with cheese curds covered in brown gravy. '),
        (40, 'Recipes', 'A quenelle is a', 'Dumpling', 'Shortbread', 'Small Game Bird', NULL, 'A', 'A quenelle is made of ground or minced fish, chicken or veal mixed with heavy cream and eggs. It is moulded into a small sausage and poached in water or stock.'),
        (40, 'Recipes', 'What are rollmops made with?', 'Herring', 'Sardines', 'Sole', NULL, 'A', 'Rollmops are pickled herring fillets rolled around a pickled onion or gherkin. The name comes from the German word "rollen," which means "to roll," and "Mops," which refers to a pug dog.'),
        (40, 'Recipes', 'Saltimbocca is an Italian dish whose name literally means', 'Dances On The Tongue', 'Fresh Catch Of The Sea', 'Leap Into The Mouth', NULL, 'C', NULL),
        (40, 'Recipes', 'The Indian snack samosa always contains', 'Meat', 'Potatoes', 'Rice', NULL, 'B', 'This fried stuffed pastry is usually vegetarian, but it can also be stuffed with meat such as ground lamb. '),
        (40, 'Recipes', 'Which of the following is an ingredient of Scotch broth?', 'Barley', 'Oats', 'Rice', NULL, 'A', 'Scotch broth also includes lamb or mutton and various vegetables. '),
        (40, 'Recipes', 'What is shashlik?', 'Hot Pepper Condiment', 'Kebab', 'Lamb Stew', NULL, 'B', 'Shashlik (sometimes spelled shashlyk), a Russian dish that originated in Georgia, consists of cubes of marinated and grilled meat and vegetables. '),
        (40, 'Recipes', 'What is socca, a local specialty of southeastern France, especially Nice?', 'An Anise-Based Cocktail', 'Chickpea Flour', 'Fish Pie', NULL, 'B', 'Socca is made into a thick porridge, which can be cooked au gratin, used in a tart, or sliced and fried in olive oil and served with sugar. '),
        (40, 'Recipes', 'Which of the following is a baked dish of spaghetti, chicken and a sherry-parmesan cream sauce, topped with parmesan and bread crumbs', 'Marengo', 'Taleggio', 'Tetrazzini', NULL, 'C', 'Turkey is sometimes substituted for chicken in this dish. '),
        (40, 'Recipes', 'Veal piccata is a classic Italian dish made with', 'Cream', 'Lemon', 'Raisins', NULL, 'B', 'The veal escalope is sautéed and served with a sauce of pan drippings, lemon juice and parsley. '),
        (40, 'Sauce', 'What is aspic?', 'Meat Seasoning', 'Savory Jelly', 'Type Of Frosting', NULL, 'B', 'Aspic is made from meat stock and gelatin. The latter allows it to set and be used in moulds with meats and vegetables.'),
        (40, 'Sauce', 'Chateaubriand is usually served with which classic sauce?', 'Béarnaise', 'Béchamel', 'Hollandaise', NULL, 'A', 'This is a classic French sauce made with a reduction of vinegar, wine, tarragon and shallots, and finished with egg yolks and butter. '),
        (40, 'Sauce', 'What kind of stock is used to make Bercy sauce?', 'Chicken', 'Fish', 'Lamb', NULL, 'B', 'White wine and shallots are also included. Bercy is a district in Paris that once had the largest wine market in Europe.'),
        (40, 'Sauce', 'In cooking, beurre manié is primarily used to', 'Flavor', 'Sweeten', 'Thicken', NULL, 'C', 'Beurre manié is a dough of soft butter and flour that is used to thicken soups and sauces. It is different from a roux in that it is not cooked before use.'),
        (40, 'Sauce', 'Which sauce contains orange juice and orange liqueur?', 'Bigarade', 'Cumberland', 'Velouté', NULL, 'A', 'Bigarade is another word for a sour orange. A bigarade sauce is a brown sauce to which orange has been added.'),
        (40, 'Sauce', 'Bigarade sauce is usually served with', 'Duck', 'Rabbit', 'Veal', NULL, 'A', 'Bigarade is prepared with bitter orange zest, lemon juice, stock and sugar. '),
        (40, 'Sauce', 'Choron sauce is a variation on which sauce?', 'Beárnaise', 'Béchamel', 'Bourguignonne', NULL, 'A', 'Choron sauce is flavored and colored with tomato paste. '),
        (40, 'Sauce', 'Cumberland sauce is made of red currant jelly and which of the following alcoholic beverages?', 'Cognac', 'Port', 'Sherry', NULL, 'B', NULL),
        (40, 'Sauce', 'What is fumet?', 'Fish Stock', 'French Smoked Sausage', 'A Whisk', NULL, 'A', 'Literally meaning "aroma" in French, a fumet is a reduced stock or cooking liquid that is added to another sauce or dish to enhance the flavor. '),
        (40, 'Sauce', 'Which of the following is the base for Hoisin sauce?', 'Fish Sauce', 'Oyster Sauce', 'Soy Sauce', NULL, 'C', 'Garlic, chili peppers, sugar and various spices are also added. '),
        (40, 'Sauce', 'Lyonnaise sauce is made with white wine, demi-glace and which of the following?', 'Celery', 'Green Peppers', 'Onions', NULL, 'C', 'Lyonnaise sauce is characterized by onions, which are sautéed until they are golden. The sauce is strained before serving.'),
        (40, 'Sauce', 'A highly seasoned sauce made with tomatoes, oregano, garlic and onions is called', 'Bercy', 'Marinara', 'Mousseline', NULL, 'B', 'This popular Italian sauce originated in Naples. Though its name is derived from the Italian word for "sailor" ("marinaro"), marinara sauce does not contain fish or seafood.'),
        (40, 'Sauce', 'Melba sauce was created by which famous chef?', 'Paul Bocuse', 'Julia Child', 'Auguste Escoffier', NULL, 'C', 'He created the sauce in 1892 when he was a chef at the Savoy in London in honor of Dame Nellie Melba. '),
        (40, 'Sauce', 'Orgeat syrup is made with sugar, rose- or orange-flavored water and which of the following?', 'Almonds', 'Peppermint', 'Pistachios', NULL, 'A', NULL),
        (40, 'Sauce', 'Redeye gravy, a sauce from the southern US, is made with', 'Bone Marrow', 'Bourbon', 'Ham Drippings', NULL, 'C', 'Redeye gravy is often served over ham, cornbread, biscuits or grits. '),
        (40, 'Sauce', 'Which of the following is the main ingredient in Indonesian satay sauce?', 'Oyster Extract', 'Peanuts', 'Red Peppers', NULL, 'B', 'Satay is usually spicy and accompanies grilled or broiled skewers of marinated cubes of meat, fish or poultry. '),
        (40, 'Sauce', 'Worcestershire sauce is a British adaptation of a recipe from which country?', 'India', 'Jamaica', 'Nigeria', NULL, 'A', 'Sir Marcus Sandys, of Worcestershire, England, discovered the recipe and asked the English grocers Lea & Perrins to make it commercially. They did, and Worcestershire sauce was launched commercially in 1838.'),
        (40, 'Sauce', 'Yakitori refers to which of the following?', 'Deep-Fried Fish', 'Grilled Chicken', 'Lightly Grilled Vegetables', NULL, 'B', 'Yakitori is a Japanese word meaning "grilled" ("yaki") "fowl" ("tori"). '),
        (40, 'Sauce', 'Which of the following is an ingredient in zingara sauce?', 'Cream', 'Lemon', 'Tomato', NULL, 'C', 'This rich tomato sauce also contains meat, paprika and chili peppers, and may be garnished with strips of ham and truffles. "Zingara" means "gypsy woman" in Italian.'),
        (40, 'Science', 'Which is the least allergenic of all fruits?', 'Apples', 'Bananas', 'Pears', NULL, 'C', NULL),
        (40, 'Science', 'Carotene, a natural orange pigment found in carrots, dark green vegetables and butter, is converted into what when consumed?', 'Vitamin A', 'Vitamin B', 'Vitamin D', NULL, 'A', 'Carotene is not lost in cooking because it is not water soluble and is heat stable. '),
        (40, 'Science', 'In 1912, Wilbur Scoville devised a means of testing the', 'Calories In Processed Food', 'Heat Level Of Peppers', 'Vitamin Content Of Fruits And Vegetables', NULL, 'B', 'The Scoville rating ranges from 0 for sweet bell peppers to 1,041,000 for the naga jolokia pepper, from India, which in 2007 was named the hottest pepper in the world by the Guinness Book of World Records. '),
        (40, 'Science', 'In what year was Vitamin C first extracted and isolated?', '1898', '1928', '1951', NULL, 'B', 'Components were extracted from lemon juice, and vitamin C was synthesized the following year. '),
        (40, 'Seafood', 'What foods are usually cooked à la nage?', 'Eggs', 'Seafood', 'Vegetables', NULL, 'B', 'The seafood is poached in a court-bouillon or vegetable stock. À la nage literally means "swimming" in French.'),
        (40, 'Seafood', 'Which of the following is a kind of fish?', 'Bream', 'Colcannon', 'Kuchen', NULL, 'A', 'This Japanese fish is also known as porgy (American) or daurade (French). '),
        (40, 'Seafood', 'Caviar is the salted roe or spawn of which fish?', 'Halibut', 'Sturgeon', 'Tuna', NULL, 'B', 'Caviar is sturgeons\' eggs that have been salted and allowed to mature. Russian caviar is the most prized.'),
        (40, 'Seafood', 'Ounce for ounce, caviar contains how much calcium compared to milk?', 'Half ', 'Same', 'Twice As Much', NULL, 'C', 'Caviar is also high in fat, cholesterol and protein, and extremely high in sodium. '),
        (40, 'Seafood', 'Which fish is NOT a relative of the cod?', 'Haddock ', 'Hake', 'Tuna', NULL, 'C', NULL),
        (40, 'Seafood', 'Cuttlefish most resembles which of the following?', 'Flounder ', 'Squid', 'Swordfish', NULL, 'B', 'A cuttlefish has ten appendages (eight arms and two long tentacles) and can measure up to 16 inches in length. '),
        (40, 'Seafood', 'Which of the following Japanese dishes can cause death if it is prepared incorrectly?', 'Fugu', 'Maguro', 'Yakitori', NULL, 'A', 'This dish is prepared from the blowfish, globefish or puffer fish, whose organs contain a deadly poison. Only licensed cooks are allowed to prepare fugu.'),
        (40, 'Seafood', 'Which of the following is NOT a flat fish?', 'Haddock', 'Sole', 'Turbot', NULL, 'A', 'Haddock is a round sea fish. '),
        (40, 'Seafood', 'Which of the following is NOT a flat fish?', 'Hake', 'Halibut', 'Sole', NULL, 'A', 'Hake, a member of the cod family, is a sea fish with a long cylindrical body that can measure up to three feet and weigh up to nine pounds. '),
        (40, 'Seafood', 'Which fish has been referred to as the "two-eyed steak"?', 'Herring', 'Salmon', 'Tuna', NULL, 'A', NULL),
        (40, 'Seafood', 'Isinglass is a type of what?', 'Crystal Stemware', 'Gelatin', 'Wine', NULL, 'B', 'Isinglass is a whitish pure gelatin prepared from the air bladders of fish (for example, sturgeon). It is used as a clarifying agent in jellies and glue. In the past it was used to clarify wines. '),
        (40, 'Seafood', 'Which of the following does NOT belong?', 'Lamprey', 'Panaché', 'Shandy', NULL, 'A', 'Lamprey is an eel-like fish. Panaché and shandy are beer-based drinks flavored in equal measures with lemonade or ginger ale.'),
        (40, 'Seafood', 'Which of the following is the smallest variety of clam?', 'Cherrystone ', 'Geoduck', 'Littleneck', NULL, 'C', 'These small clams measure about two inches in diameter. '),
        (40, 'Seafood', 'Petit-gris is a kind of', 'Clam', 'Grape', 'Snail', NULL, 'C', 'This small gray snail measures about one inch in diameter. '),
        (40, 'Seafood', 'Which of the following is NOT a type of fish?', 'Scallops', 'Smelts', 'Tilapia', NULL, 'A', 'Scallops are bi-valve mollusks. '),
        (40, 'Seafood', 'Shad and alewife are members of which family of fish?', 'Bass', 'Herring', 'Salmon', NULL, 'B', 'Both are anadromous, which means that they migrate from salt water to spawn in fresh water. '),
        (40, 'Seafood', 'Tomalley is found in the liver of which of the following?', 'Cod', 'Lobster', 'Sturgeon', NULL, 'B', 'Tomalley is the soft green substance found in the liver of lobsters. Considered a delicacy, it can be eaten alone or added to sauces.'),
        (40, 'Seafood', 'Whitebait are very young', 'Herring', 'Sardines', 'Smelt', NULL, 'A', 'These small fish are usually fried and eaten whole. '),
        (40, 'Service', 'The table fork was introduced in England in', '1501', '1608', '1701', NULL, 'B', 'Until then, people ate with knives, spoons or their hands. '),
        (40, 'Service', 'What type of service involves finishing the preparation of food at the table rather than in the kitchen?', 'American', 'French', 'Russian', NULL, 'B', NULL),
        (40, 'Service', 'In French service, gueridon refers to which of the following?', 'A Serving Platter', 'A Serving Utensil', 'A Side Cart', NULL, 'C', 'One purpose of the gueridon is to keep food and plates warm. '),
        (40, 'Service', 'To what person should the sommelier offer the first taste of wine?', 'The Oldest Woman', 'The Person Who Made The Reservation', 'The Person Who Ordered The Wine', NULL, 'C', NULL),
        (40, 'Soup', 'At its most basic, a bisque is a rich soup made with which of the following?', 'Cream', 'Shellfish', 'Sherry Or Port', NULL, 'A', 'The other ingredients are optional. '),
        (40, 'Soup', 'A popular American turtle soup is called which of the following?', 'Billi-Bi', 'Boula Boula', 'Callaloo', NULL, 'B', 'Billi-bi (also billy-bi) is a cold mussel soup. Callaloo is a fish soup from South America.'),
        (40, 'Soup', 'Which of the following soups is NOT made with seafood?', 'Bourride', 'Cioppino', 'Garbure', NULL, 'C', 'Garbure is a thick vegetable stew that often also contains bacon, pork or sausage. '),
        (40, 'soup', 'Potage Parmentier is a soup made with', 'Leek And Potato', 'Mushrooms And Onion', 'Spinach And Bacon', NULL, 'A', 'Cream and sometimes chicken stock are also included. The soup is named after Antoine Parmentier (1737–1833), a French agronomist who championed the potato in France.'),
        (40, 'soup', 'In Dutch cuisine "snert" refers to a', 'Porridge', 'Sardine', 'Soup', NULL, 'C', 'This thick green pea soup, usually a meal in itself, also contains pork, celeriac, celery, onions, potatoes and sausage. '),
        (40, 'Spirits', 'The Latin term "aqua vitae" (water of life) was used in ancient times to describe which of the following?', 'Beer', 'Spirits', 'Wine', NULL, 'B', NULL),
        (30, 'Spirits', 'True or false? Bottles of brandy should be stored on their side, just as wine is, to ensure proper ageing. ', 'True', 'False', NULL, NULL, 'B', 'The bottles must be kept upright to avoid contact between the brandy and the cork. This also applies to scotch and other whiskies.'),
        (30, 'Spirits', 'True or false? Cognac and Armagnac improve in the bottle after barrel ageing.  ', 'True', 'False', NULL, NULL, 'B', 'However, once opened, Cognac and Armagnac will keep for a considerable time without deteriorating. '),
        (40, 'Spirits', 'The term "dunder" is associated with the', 'Brewing Of Beer', 'Making Of Rum', 'Production Of Cheese', NULL, 'B', 'Dunder is the yeast-rich leftovers from rum that are used to start the yeast culture of another batch. '),
        (40, 'Spirits', 'What berry is gin made from?', 'Blackberry', 'Cranberry', 'Juniper', NULL, 'C', 'Though too bitter to eat raw, the pungent darkish berries of the juniper tree are used in cooking and for making spirits. Juniper berry oils have diuretic properties that help flush out the urinary system.'),
        (40, 'Spirits', 'Irish whiskey has been referred to as the', 'Elixir Of The Gods', 'Mother\'S Milk', 'Water Of Life', NULL, 'C', NULL),
        (40, 'Spirits', 'Which of the following does NOT belong?', 'Chartreuse', 'Izarra', 'Kahlua', NULL, 'C', 'Chartreuse and Izarra are herbal-based liqueurs that come in two types: yellow and green. They are higher proof than Kahlua, which is a coffee-based liqueur.'),
        (40, 'Spirits', 'What spirit is made from fermented ripe cherries?', 'Calvados', 'Chambord', 'Kirsch', NULL, 'C', NULL),
        (40, 'Spirits', 'Which of the following spices characterizes Kümmel schnapps?', 'Caraway', 'Cinnamon', 'Nutmeg', NULL, 'A', 'Though it probably dates to 16th century Holland, Kümmel is a specialty of northern European countries. '),
        (40, 'Spirits', 'From the perspective of a connoisseur, which of the following is the best way to enjoy whiskey?', 'Neat', 'On The Rocks', 'With Soda', NULL, 'A', 'Or with a few drops of room-temperature water. Chilling the whiskey with ice dulls the flavor instead of enhancing it.'),
        (40, 'Spirits', 'In bartending, a "pony" refers to which measurement?', 'One Ounce', 'One And A Half Ounces', 'Two Ounces', NULL, 'A', 'A pony is also known as a "shot" or a "jigger. '),
        (40, 'Spirits', 'The USA still uses the proof system to express the percentage of alcohol by volume. 100 proof is equal to what percentage?', '45 Per Cent', '50 Per Cent', '100 Per Cent', NULL, 'B', NULL),
        (40, 'Spirits', 'What country produces rums that are best known for their dark style?', 'Barbados', 'Cuba', 'Jamaica', NULL, 'C', 'The general style of Jamaican rum is rich, dark, heavy and pungent. Barbadian rums are semi-light, and Cuban rums are light and delicate.'),
        (40, 'Spirits', 'From what area in Scotland do we get the single malt scotches Laphroaig, Lagavulin and Bruichladdich?', 'Campbeltown', 'Islay', 'Lowland', NULL, 'B', NULL),
        (40, 'Spirits', 'In what year were blended Scotch whiskies were first introduced?', '1853', '1608', '1922', NULL, 'A', 'The Edinburgh firm Andrew Usher and Company released the first batch of vatted malt (a blend of whiskies of different ages) in 1853; it was called Old Vatted Glenlivet Whisky. '),
        (40, 'Spirits', 'Which of the following would usually be included in turtle soup?', 'Cognac', 'Madeira', 'White Wine', NULL, 'B', 'Sherry is also commonly used. '),
        (40, 'Statistics', 'According to the Guinness Book of World Records, what country has the largest restaurant (seating) in the world?', 'Hong Kong', 'Russia', 'Syria', NULL, 'C', 'The Damascus Gate restaurant, in Damascus, can seat 6,014 people. During peak operation, it employs 1,800 staff. The restaurant features such things as waterfalls, fountains and replicas of archeological ruins of Syria. '),
        (40, 'Statistics', 'Where does the US restaurant industry rank with respect to the size of its workforce?', 'First', 'Second', 'Third', NULL, 'A', NULL),
        (40, 'Statistics', 'What percentage of land in Italy is covered by farmland?', '80 Per Cent', '50 Per Cent', '20 Per Cent', NULL, 'C', NULL),
        (40, 'Statistics', 'Which country consumes the most wine per capita?', 'France', 'Italy', 'Luxembourg', NULL, 'A', 'Luxembourg is second. '),
        (40, 'Techniques', 'Who is credited with creating the professional kitchen as we know it today?', 'Jean-Anthelme Brillat-Savarin', 'Antonin Carême', 'Auguste Escoffier', NULL, 'C', 'His kitchen was organized by sections, run by chefs de partie. His "brigade system" was likely a result of his experience as an army chef in the Franco–Prussian war.'),
        (40, 'Techniques', 'Deglazing refers to which of the following?', 'Icing For Cakes', 'Making A Sauce For Meats', 'Topping For Patés', NULL, 'B', 'Deglazing refers to the technique of adding a liquid (e. g., wine) to a pan to dissolve caramelized bits of food. '),
        (40, 'Techniques', 'If a fish is described as "drawn," it means that it', 'Is Served With Butter', 'Has Been Gutted', 'Has Been Weighed At The Dock', NULL, 'B', NULL),
        (40, 'Techniques', 'Julienning is a method of food preparation in which food is', 'Cut Into Small Cubes', 'Cut Into Thin Strips', 'Finely Diced', NULL, 'B', 'Carrots are often julienned as are potatoes to make thin french fries. '),
        (40, 'Terms', 'In the 17th century, which of the following words referred to an incongruous mixture of liquids that would not ordinarily go together?', 'Balderdash', 'Hodgepodge', 'Mishmash', NULL, 'A', 'This word appeared around the time of Shakespeare; an example of balderdash is beer and buttermilk, or wine and beer. '),
        (40, 'Trivia', 'Who said, "Always do sober what you said you\'d do drunk. That will teach you to keep your mouth shut"?', 'Ozzie Osbourne', 'Johnny Depp', 'Ernest Hemingway', NULL, 'C', NULL),
        (40, 'Trivia', 'Frederick the Great reportedly made his coffee with', 'Beer', 'Brandy', 'Champagne', NULL, 'C', NULL),
        (40, 'Trivia', 'Who said, "The consumption of alcohol may create the illusion that you are tougher, smarter, faster and better looking than most people"?', 'George Carlin', 'Chris Rock', 'Henny Youngman', NULL, 'C', NULL),
        (40, 'Utensils', 'In French cooking, what does "cocotte" refer to?', 'A Casserole', 'An Egg Holder', 'A Fine Strainer', NULL, 'A', 'A cocotte is both a baking dish and the ingredients it contains. Watch how you use it, though — "cocotte" can also mean "prostitute" or "floozy.'),
        (40, 'Utensils', 'In Spain, a copita is a', 'Deep Fried Fish Snack', 'Sherry Glass', 'Type Of Flatbread', NULL, 'B', 'This traditional glass originated in Jerez, Spain. '),
        (40, 'Utensils', 'What is a mezzaluna?', 'A Blade For Chopping', 'A Double Boiler', 'A Vegetable Peeler', NULL, 'A', 'A mezzaluna is a crescent-shaped blade with wooden knobs at each end; the cook rocks it back and forth on a cutting board. "Mezzaluna" means "half-moon" in Italian.'),
        (40, 'Utensils', 'In what year did the first commercial microwave hit the market?', '1947', '1959', '1964', NULL, 'A', 'It was manufactured by the Massachusetts company Raytheon. Called the Radarange range, the oven was 5 1/2 ft. R543 tall, weighed 750 lbs and cost $5,000. Today Raytheon is the world\'s largest producer of guided missiles.'),
        (40, 'Utensils', 'How many tablespoons are there in one fluid ounce?', 'One', 'Two', 'Three', NULL, 'B', NULL),
        (40, 'Vegetables', 'Allonya is a kind of', 'Ground Nut', 'Miniature Banana', 'Yam', NULL, 'C', 'Allonyas are starchy yam tubers common in Caribbean cooking. '),
        (40, 'Vegetables', 'Which of the following is a type of Italian rice?', 'Arborio', 'Bruschetta', 'Minestra', NULL, 'A', 'This short-grained rice is high in starch and is especially good for making risotto. '),
        (40, 'Vegetables', 'To which vegetable family does arugula belong?', 'Cabbage', 'Mustard', 'Parsley', NULL, 'B', 'Arugula is an aromatic salad green with a peppery mustard flavor. '),
        (40, 'Vegetables', 'How is white asparagus produced?', 'By Crossing It With White Eggplant', 'By Growing Green Asparagus In The Dark', 'By Harvesting It Early', NULL, 'B', NULL),
        (40, 'Vegetables', 'Which food is the least stable in the cupboard?', 'Dried Beans', 'Pasta', 'Plain Rice', NULL, 'A', 'After one year, the soaking times of dried beans can increase significantly. Pasta and rice can be stored for several years without loss of quality.'),
        (40, 'Vegetables', 'Cardoons are a close relative of which vegetable?', 'Artichoke', 'Okra', 'Radish', NULL, 'A', 'The cardoon, which is popular in France, Spain and Italy, is available at the end of autumn and in winter. The stalks are especially good fried. They can also be served cold, with vinaigrette. '),
        (40, 'Vegetables', 'Tomatoes are a member of the nightshade family, Solanaceae. Which of the following is NOT a member of the same family?', 'Carrots', 'Eggplants', 'Potatoes', NULL, 'A', NULL),
        (40, 'Vegetables', 'What is an alternative name for cassava?', 'Yam', 'Yarrow', 'Yuca', NULL, 'C', 'This starchy plant is similar to potatoes in nutrition and is best known for its association with tapioca. '),
        (40, 'Vegetables', 'Which of the following resembles a turnip?', 'Cardoon', 'Celeriac', 'Tomato', NULL, 'B', 'This root vegetable can be peeled, cut into small pieces, boiled until tender and served with butter or sauce. '),
        (40, 'Vegetables', 'A cep is a kind of', 'Bean', 'Mushroom', 'Pastry', NULL, 'B', 'This large mushroom has a brown cap, a thick white stem and an aroma reminiscent of sourdough. '),
        (40, 'Vegetables', 'Which of the following tastes like licorice?', 'Cardoon', 'Celeriac', 'Fennel', NULL, 'C', 'Fennel resembles celery. Its stems can be eaten cooked or uncooked, and it goes well with apple and nuts.'),
        (40, 'Vegetables', 'A gherkin is the same thing as which of the following?', 'Bresaola', 'Cornichon', 'Flageolet', NULL, 'B', 'Gherkins and cornichons are small tart pickles. '),
        (40, 'Vegetables', 'What is maize?', 'Barley', 'Corn', 'Wheat', NULL, 'B', 'Maize is known as corn in the US and Canada. Christopher Columbus discovered it, and Cortés introduced it to Europe.'),
        (40, 'Vegetables', 'The world\'s largest exporter of mustard seeds is', 'Canada', 'Poland', 'Russia', NULL, 'A', NULL),
        (40, 'Vegetables', 'Which of the following is NOT a member of the cabbage family?', 'Kale', 'Kohlrabi', 'Okra', NULL, 'C', NULL),
        (40, 'Vegetables', 'Picholine, gaeta and niçoise are all types of', 'Capers', 'Mushrooms', 'Olives', NULL, 'C', NULL),
        (40, 'Vegetables', 'Which of the following is NOT native to the Americas?', 'Corn', 'Parsnips', 'Tomatoes', NULL, 'B', 'The parsnip was brought to North America from Europe in the early 17th century. The parsnip is used in all the same ways as the turnip, and can also be baked or cooked like carrots.'),
        (40, 'Vegetables', 'Greening in potatoes is caused by which of the following?', 'Excess Moisture', 'Exposure To Light', 'High Acidity In Soil', NULL, 'B', 'Greening indicates the presence of an alkaloid called solanine, which is toxic in large amounts. '),
        (30, 'Vegetables', 'True or false? Sorrel has a peppery flavor.   ', 'True', 'False', NULL, NULL, 'B', 'The herb sorrel contains oxalic acid, which imparts a sharp or acidic taste. Because of this it is usually parblanched before cooking.'),
        (40, 'Vegetables', 'Which plant provides a complete protein source?', 'Barley', 'Peanut', 'Soybean', NULL, 'C', NULL),
        (40, 'Vegetables', 'Swede and neep are terms used in Britain, particularly in Scotland, to refer to', 'Rabbit Stew', 'Sardines', 'Turnips', NULL, 'C', NULL),
        (40, 'Vegetables', 'Which food is referred to as "meat without bones"?', 'Breadfruit', 'Cassava', 'Tofu', NULL, 'C', 'Also known as doufo in China, bean curd is relatively high in protein (over 10 per cent in firm tofu). It also contains iron and has little fat.'),
        (40, 'Wine', 'Which grape is NOT entitled to enjoy the status of Appellation d’origine contrôlée in Alsace?', 'Gewurztraminer', 'Pinot Blanc', 'Sauvignon Blanc', NULL, 'C', NULL),
        (40, 'Wine', 'What does "amaro" mean in Italian?', 'Bitter', 'Hot', 'Spicy', NULL, 'A', NULL),
        (40, 'Wine', 'Bandol is a wine from which region in France?', 'Bordeaux', 'Burgundy', 'Provence', NULL, 'C', 'This dark red wine is made from the Mourvèdre grape as well as from other local varieties. '),
        (40, 'Wine', 'What does the German word "Bereich" refer to?', 'Wine Barrel', 'Wine Region', 'Winery', NULL, 'B', 'Bereich refers to a rather broad area usually incorporating a number of neighboring villages and vineyards. '),
        (40, 'Wine', 'What is the most southerly French wine region?', 'Alsace', 'Bordeaux', 'Champagne', NULL, 'B', NULL),
        (40, 'Wine', 'Generally speaking, if a wine is described as tannic with flavors of chocolate, black currants and tobacco, it is likely made from which grape?', 'Cabernet', 'Merlot', 'Zinfandel', NULL, 'A', 'The intensity of the flavors may vary, however, depending on where the grapes were grown. '),
        (40, 'Wine', 'Chenin Blanc is an important grape in', 'Alsace', 'Burgundy', 'The Loire Valley', NULL, 'C', 'Vouvray and Bonnezeaux are two great Chenin-based Loire Valley wines. '),
        (40, 'Wine', 'The Pinotage grape is a cross between Pinot Noir and which of the following grapes?', 'Cinsault', 'Grenache', 'Malbec', NULL, 'A', 'It is grown commercially in South Africa and makes a dark, fruity wine with an earthy character often described as "paintbox. '),
        (40, 'Wine', 'Red wine is usually in its prime when it is ', 'Red', 'Red With Tinges Of Brown And Orange', 'Purple', NULL, 'B', NULL),
        (40, 'Wine', 'What is Australia\'s famous wine district Coonawarra famous for?', 'Black Volcanic Soil', 'Red Soil', 'Yellow Sandy Soil', NULL, 'B', 'Coonawarra is an Aboriginal word meaning "honeysuckle. '),
        (40, 'Wine', 'What does the Spanish word "cosecha" mean with reference to wine?', 'Aged In Oak', 'Slightly Sweet', 'Vintage', NULL, 'C', NULL),
        (40, 'Wine', 'In Italy, DOC wines (controlled name and region) account for what percentage of total production?', '10 Per Cent', '25 Per Cent', '75 Per Cent', NULL, 'B', NULL),
        (40, 'Wine', 'When the word "finish" is used with respect to wine, it refers to a', 'Final Wine-Making Step Before Bottling', 'Lingering Sensation After You Taste The Wine', 'Last Sip Of Wine', NULL, 'B', NULL),
        (40, 'Wine', 'What does "gallo" mean in Italian?', 'Robust', 'Rooster', 'Royal', NULL, 'B', 'A rooster is the symbol of Chianti Classico, which was acclaimed by Grand Duke Cosimo III de Medici in 1716. '),
        (40, 'Wine', 'What percentage of German wines are white?', '65 Per Cent', '85 Per Cent', '95 Per Cent', NULL, 'B', 'The famous white grape Riesling accounts for about 22 per cent of vine plantings in Germany. '),
        (40, 'Wine', 'In Spain, Gran Reserva wines must be aged a minimum of how many years?', 'Three', 'Five', 'Seven', NULL, 'B', 'This includes at least two years in casks. '),
        (40, 'Wine', 'Hermitage is a French wine from which of the following areas?', 'Alsace', 'Côtes Du Rhône', 'The Loire Valley', NULL, 'B', 'This area produces both red and white wines. '),
        (40, 'Wine', 'When referring to wine, what does the term "lees" mean?', 'Sediment', 'Stacking Of Barrels', 'Vineyard Orientation', NULL, 'A', 'Lees are the solid particles found at the bottom of the vat after fermentation. '),
        (40, 'Wine', 'How many liters of champagne are there in a magnum?', 'One', 'One And A Half', 'Two', NULL, 'B', NULL),
        (40, 'Wine', 'In which region of Australia is the Margaret River wine area found?', 'New South Wales', 'South Australia', 'Western Australia', NULL, 'C', 'Margaret River enjoys an excellent reputation for Cabernet Sauvignon. '),
        (40, 'Wine', 'When talking about wine, the term "meniscus" refers to', 'The Amount Of Time For Fermentation To Finish', 'The Ratio Of Acid To Sugar In A Wine', 'The Rim Of Wine That Touches The Surface Of A Wine Glass', NULL, 'C', 'The color intensity of the meniscus can indicate how concentrated the wine is. '),
        (40, 'Wine', 'Nuits-Saint-Georges is a wine appellation from', 'Bordeaux', 'Burgundy', 'The Rhône Valley', NULL, 'B', 'Nuit-Saint-Georges extends from south of Dijon to the edge of Côte de Beaune and produces mainly red wines known for their elegance and robust flavor. '),
        (40, 'Wine', 'Opus One is a high-end wine from California\'s Napa Valley. The main grape in this wine is', 'Cabernet Sauvignon', 'Merlot', 'Zinfandel', NULL, 'A', 'Other Bordeaux grapes are also included. The winery, also called Opus One, is a joint venture of Baron Philippe de Rothschild and Robert Mondavi.'),
        (40, 'Wine', 'Port, Madeira and sherry have all been topped up with which of the following?', 'Alcohol', 'Bitters', 'Sugar', NULL, 'A', 'Alcohols like brandy are commonly used to top up other beverages. '),
        (40, 'Wine', 'In Germany, the designation "Pradikat" on a wine label refers to which of the following?', 'Number Of Years In Barrels', 'Ripeness Of The Grapes', 'Whether A Wine Has Been Aged In Barrels', NULL, 'B', 'This is the highest rank in the German system. '),
        (40, 'Wine', 'Quincy is the name of a wine from', 'Australia\'S Adelaide Hills', 'The Loire Valley In France', 'Oregon\'S Willamette Valley', NULL, 'B', 'Quincy is made from Sauvignon Blanc and has a rather high acidity. '),
