        (50, 'Coffee/Tea', 'What does the word "tisane" refer to?', 'Herbal Tea', 'Finger-Sized Pastry', 'Spice Mixture', 'Vodka-Based Cocktail ', 'A', 'A tisane is made by steeping herbs, spices and/or flowers in boiling water. Many tisanes are made for medicinal purposes (for example, camomile is said to be useful against headaches; mint is a tonic).'),
