        (50, 'Desserts', 'Sachertorte (Sacher torte) is made with chocolate and what kind of jam?', 'Apricot', 'Lemon', 'Peach', 'Raspberry', 'A', 'This Viennese classic was invented in 1832 by Franz Sacher for a dinner party given by Prince von Metternich. '),
        (50, 'Desserts', 'Savoiardi refers to', 'An Aperitif', 'A Biscuit', 'A Cheese', 'An Olive', 'B', 'Often referred to as ladyfingers, these light, sweet, crispy sponge cakes are about the size of a large finger and are used in trifles, charlottes and tiramisù. '),
        (50, 'Desserts', 'What is a syllabub?', 'A Fried Bacon And Cheese Sandwich', 'A Mixture Of Beer And Brandy', 'A Pot Pie Made With Partridge', 'A Thick, Frothy Dessert', 'D', 'This English concoction that dates to the time of Elizabeth І is made with milk, wine or ale, sugar, spices and egg whites. '),
        (50, 'Desserts', 'Tarte Tatin is a French dessert made with', 'Apples', 'Lemons And  Oranges', 'Peaches', 'Strawberries', 'A', 'This upside-down apple pie is made with apples caramelized in butter and sugar. '),
