        (50, 'Fruit', 'The seeds of which of the following fruits contain cyanide?', 'Apples', 'Grapefruit', 'Papaya', 'Raspberries', 'A', 'However, cyanide is present in such minute amounts that one would have to eat thousands of seeds before suffering any ill effects. '),
        (50, 'Fruit', 'In what country did apricots originate?', 'Algeria', 'China', 'India', 'Mexico', 'B', 'Apricots date to approximately 4,000 years ago. They were probably introduced to Europe by Alexander the Great.'),
