        (50, 'fruit', 'A bunch of bananas is referred to as a', 'Folly', 'Hand', 'Merry', 'Stack', 'B', NULL),
        (50, 'Fruit', 'Approximately 50 per cent of all tropical fruits produced worldwide are', 'Bananas', 'Coconuts', 'Mangos', 'Papayas', 'C', NULL),
        (50, 'Fruit', 'A mangosteen is a type of', 'Fish Chowder', 'Indonesian Coffee Bean', 'Small Goat', 'Tropical Fruit', 'D', 'The mangosteen, which is related to the mango, is native to Malaysia. It has a dark red skin and juicy white flesh.'),
        (50, 'Fruit', 'Mirabelle is a type of which fruit?', 'Apple', 'Cherry', 'Plum', 'Raspberry', 'C', 'Mirabelle plums are small and round, and range in color from golden yellow to red. They can be stewed, made into jam, preserved in syrup or used to make a white brandy.'),
        (50, 'Fruit', 'Mulberries are', 'Black', 'Red', 'White', 'All Of The Above', 'D', 'Mulberries resemble blackberries in size and shape. They grow in subtropical areas of Asia, Europe and the Americas.'),
        (50, 'Fruit', 'Pippin refers to', 'Apples', 'Peppers', 'Plums', 'Potatoes', 'A', 'Pippin now refers to various types of apples, but it originally applied to any variety of apple grown from seed. The word comes from Old French "pépin," which means "seed" or "pip.'),
        (50, 'fruit', 'Rambutan is a type of', 'Cooking Pot', 'Flat Bread', 'Fruit', 'Stew', 'C', 'The rambutan is a relative of the lychee and is common in southeast Asia, where it is eaten in salads but also served with pork dishes. Its thick red shell is coverd with hooked hairs.'),
        (50, 'Fruit', 'What is the most popular commercial apple variety in North America?', 'Granny Smith', 'Macintosh', 'Red Delicious', 'Spartan', 'C', NULL),
        (50, 'fruit', 'Which fruit has the highest percentage of sugar content by fresh weight?', 'Banana', 'Cherry', 'Honeydew', 'Pineapple', 'A', 'Bananas are 18 per cent sugar, cherries are 14 per cent, pineapples are 13 per cent, and honeydew is 10 per cent. '),
        (50, 'fruit', 'Which fruit has the lowest percentage of sugar content by fresh weight?', 'Cranberry', 'Grapefruit', 'Lemon', 'Tomato', 'C', 'Lemons are 2 per cent sugar, tomatoes are 3 per cent, cranberries are 4 per cent, and grapefruit is 6 per cent. '),
        (50, 'Fruit', 'Ugli fruit is native to which country?', 'Brazil', 'Jamaica', 'Madagascar', 'The Philippines', 'B', 'Possibly a tangerine-grapefruit hybrid, the ugli fruit\'s name derives from its unsightly wrinkled skin wrapped loosely around the pulpy citrus interior. '),
        (50, 'fruit', 'Which of the following contains the most vitamin C in mg per 100 grams of edible portion of raw item?', 'Broccoli', 'Orange', 'Strawberry', 'Tomato', 'A', 'It contains 89. 2 mg. R543 Oranges have 45, strawberries 37 and tomatoes 12. 7.'),
        (50, 'Grains', 'Quinoa is a kind of', 'Flatbread', 'Fruit', 'Grain', 'Spice', 'C', 'Quinoa has been cultivated in the Andes for thousands of years. It is an excellent source of plant protein and minerals.'),
        (50, 'Herbs/Spices', 'Which of the following is NOT one of the herbs used in bouquet garni?', 'Bay Leaf', 'Cilantro', 'Oregano', 'Parsley', 'C', 'A bouquet garni (French for "garnished bouquet")is a bundle of herbs tied together with a string or put into a sachet and used to prepare stocks, soups and stews. It can also include basil, rosemary, chervil, tarragon or savory.'),
        (50, 'Herbs/Spices', 'After saffron and vanilla, which of the following is the most expensive spice?', 'Cardamom', 'Cumin', 'Nutmeg', 'Pepper', 'A', 'This spicy, pungent spice is used in sweet and savory Middle Eastern and Indian dishes. '),
        (50, 'Herbs/Spices', 'Cynar is an Italian aperitif flavored with ', 'Artichokes', 'Figs', 'Grapefruit', 'Walnuts', 'A', 'This bitter liqueur also includes 13 other herbs and plants. Italians sip it on the rocks, often with a slice of orange, before or after meals.'),
        (50, 'Herbs/Spices', 'In Indian cuisine, "masala" refers to', 'Dried Mango', 'Chickpeas', 'A Spice Mixture', 'Stew', 'C', 'Masala can refer either to dried spices or to a paste made with spices and other ingredients such as garlic, ginger and onions. '),
        (40, 'Herbs/Spices', 'Oregano is often compared to what other herb?', 'Borage   Bergamot', 'Calumba', 'Marjoram', NULL, 'C', 'Although the marjoram and oregano plants look and taste alike, marjoram is milder and sweeter than oregano. '),
        (50, 'Herbs/Spices', 'Persillade is a culinary term for parsley and', 'Garlic', 'Paprika', 'Pepper', 'Salt', 'A', 'If the persillade is added early in cooking, it becomes mellow. When added at the end or as a garnish, it provides a garlicky zap. Persillades are common in French, Greek, Cajun, Louisiana Creole and Québecois cuisines. '),
        (50, 'Herbs/Spices', 'In French cuisine, the mixture quatre-épices (four spices) consists of pepper, nutmeg, cinnamon and', 'Cloves', 'Coriander', 'Cumin', 'Saffron', 'A', 'Quatre-épices is used to flavor terrines and pâtés. '),
        (50, 'Herbs/Spices', 'What country produces two-thirds of the world\'s vanilla?', 'India', 'Indonesia', 'Madagascar', 'Sri Lanka', 'C', 'Vanilla is native to Mexico; the Aztecs were known to have used it. The Spanish took it back to Europe, and it spread quickly around the world from there.'),
        (50, 'Herbs/Spices', 'Zaatar is a Middle Eastern', 'Almond-Based Confection', 'Butter Bean Soup', 'Lamb Kebab', 'Spice Mixture', 'D', 'Zaatar is a mixture of the herb zaatar mixed with spices. It is used as a condiment.'),
        (50, 'History', 'Carême is the name of which of the following?', 'A Coffee-Based Drink', 'A Famous Chef', 'A Type Of Icing', 'A Type Of Chocolate', 'B', 'Antonin Carême (1783–1833) is considered one of the founders of French cooking. '),
        (50, 'History', 'In 1947 Marilyn Monroe was crowned the first queen of which of the following?', 'Artichokes', 'Grapefruits', 'Kumquats', 'Oranges', 'A', 'Marilyn Monroe was 21 and still known as Norma Jean Baker when she was crowned the first Artichoke Queen of Castroville, California, which bills itself as the artichoke center of the world. '),
