        (50, 'Meat', 'Which country eats more meat per capita than any country in the world?', 'Argentina', 'France', 'Germany', 'Usa', 'A', 'Argentinians consume an average of 10 oz. of meat per person per day.'),
        (50, 'Meat', 'Culatello is a type of', 'Cheese', 'Ham', 'Pasta', 'Wine', 'B', 'Culatello is a lean, cured and aged Italian ham. '),
        (50, 'Meat', 'Who developed the flat-iron steak?', 'A Railroad Company', 'A University Research Team', 'A Us Army General', 'The Ritz Hotel In New York', 'B', 'Teams from the universities of Nebraska and Florida, using a previously waste cut of beef from the shoulder, developed a method for cutting and presenting the steak, which looks like an old-fashioned flat metal iron. '),
        (50, 'Meat', 'Foie gras comes from', 'Chickens', 'Geese', 'Pheasants', 'Turkeys', 'B', 'Foie gras is made from the liver of a goose or duck that has been force fed, a practise that dates back to the ancient Romans. The European Union as well as the city of Chicago have passed laws against force feeding geese.'),
        (50, 'Meat', 'Galantine refers to preparations made with', 'Fish', 'Pork', 'Poultry', 'Vegetables', 'C', 'A galantine is a mixture of lean ground meat and a forcemeat of eggs, spices and other ingredients pressed into a cylindrical shape. It is cooked in stock and served cold as an entree.'),
        (50, 'Meat', 'Jamon is a Spanish word for', 'Cut Of Ham', 'French Roasting Pot', 'Gooey Frosting Used On Pastries', 'Young Turkey', 'A', 'Jamon also refers to a cut of bacon. '),
        (50, 'Meat', 'Seasoned beef that is dry-cured, smoked and cooked is called', 'Carpaccio', 'Mortadella', 'Pastrami', 'Prosciutto', 'C', NULL),
        (50, 'Meat', 'Squab is a type of ', 'Asian Fruit', 'Bird', 'Saltwater Fish', 'Clam', 'B', 'A squab is a domesticated pigeon that has never flown and, therefore, has very tender meat. '),
        (50, 'Meat', 'Wagyu refers to', 'Beef', 'Noodles', 'Radish', 'Tuna', 'A', 'Japanese Wagyu cattle are genetically predisposed to produce highly marbled meat that is extremely tender and flavorful. '),
        (50, 'Meat', 'Westphalian ham is a cured and smoked ham produced from pigs raised on which of the following?', 'Acorns', 'Chestnuts', 'Corn', 'Sweet Potatoes', 'A', 'This excellent German ham is dense, dark brown and among the best in the world. '),
        (50, 'Misc.', 'Canned food was first produced because of the encouragement of', 'Thomas Jefferson', 'Napoleon Bonaparte', 'Lord Nelson', 'Czar Nicholas Ii Of Russia', 'B', 'During the Napoleonic wars, Napoleon offered a prize to whoever could invent a method of preventing food from spoiling. The winner, Nicolas Appert, used jars that were packed with food and sealed, then boiled to prevent spoilage.'),
        (50, 'Misc.', 'For every dollar spent in the US on produce at the supermarket, how much goes to the farmer who produced the food?', '5 Cents', '10 Cents', '15 Cents', '20 Cents', 'A', NULL),
        (50, 'Misc.', 'What does the Japanese word "kanpai" refer to?', 'A Toast (As In What One Says Before Taking A Drink)', 'A Strongly Flavored Rice Liqueur', 'The Headgear Worn By Chefs', 'Saki Bar', 'A', NULL),
        (50, 'Nuts', 'The cashew is native to which country?', 'Brazil', 'India', 'Mexico', 'Madagascar', 'A', 'Cashews were introduced to other tropical countries in the 16th century. '),
        (50, 'Nuts', 'Cashew nuts hang from fleshy fruitlike peduncles that are sometimes referred to as', 'Apples', 'Bananas', 'Melons', 'Pears', 'A', NULL),
        (50, 'Nuts', 'In its natural state, which nut contains a potent skin irritant that must be roasted in order to remove it and make the nut safe to eat?', 'Brazil Nuts', 'Cashews', 'Hazelnuts', 'Macadamia', 'B', NULL),
        (50, 'Nuts', 'Goobers are also known as', 'Jelly Beans', 'Peanuts', 'Tiny Shrimp', 'Unpopped Popcorn', 'B', 'Other names include pindars, ground nuts, monkey nuts, grass nuts, earth nuts and goober peas. '),
        (50, 'Oils', 'Which of the following oils has the highest smoke point (the temperature at which oil burns)?', 'Avocado Oil', 'Coconut Oil', 'Grapeseed Oil', 'Sesame Oil', 'A', 'The smoke point of avocado oil is 520°F (271°C). '),
        (50, 'Oils', 'Which of the following attributes part of its name to Canada?', 'Canapé', 'Can', 'Canola', 'Cantaloupe', 'C', 'Can for Canada and "ola" for oil low acid. Rapeseed oil was used as industrial oil for hundreds of years.'),
        (50, 'Oils', 'Which of the following oils is high in saturated fat?', 'Canola', 'Corn', 'Palm', 'Peanut', 'C', 'Palm oil contains saturated fat and is semi-solid at room temperature. However, it also contains a high amount of beta-carotene, antioxidants and vitamin E.'),
        (50, 'Oils', 'Which of the following makes up over 50 per cent of the world\'s oil and fat exports?', 'Palm', 'Canola (Rapeseed)', 'Soybean', 'Sunflower', 'A', 'Soybean accounts for only 19 per cent. '),
        (50, 'Pasta', 'Orzo means which of the following in Italian?', 'Barley', 'Nut', 'Rice', 'Wheat', 'A', 'In North America, orzo is commonly understood as a rice-shaped pasta. '),
        (50, 'Processed Foods', 'Gnocchi is a kind of', 'Brandy', 'Dessert', 'Pasta', 'Salami', 'C', 'Gnocchi are small dumplings, usually made of flour, semolina or potato. They are boiled and served with sauce or baked. Gnocchi means "lumps" in Italian. '),
        (50, 'Recipes', 'À la Clamart refers to dishes garnished with which of the following?', 'Beets', 'Carrots', 'Peas', 'Asparagus', 'C', 'Clamart is a district near the Seine River, in France, that used to be famous for its pea crops. '),
        (50, 'Recipes', 'What is achar?', 'Chili Pepper', 'Poached Fish Preparation', 'Spiced Pickle', 'Spice Mixture', 'C', 'Achar is popular throughout the East and West Indies. Some achars are spicy; some mild and sweet.'),
        (50, 'Recipes', 'Blinis are a dish from', 'Germany', 'Hungary', 'Poland', 'Russia', 'D', 'Blinis are small pancakes served with sour cream and caviar. '),
        (50, 'Recipes', 'What is burek?', 'Fried Fish', 'Stuffed Pastry', 'Lamb Kebab', 'Pistachio And Honey Confection', 'B', 'Burek is popular in Arab countries and in countries around the Mediterranean. It consists of filo pastry filled with cheese, meat or vegetables. It is baked or fried. '),
        (50, 'Recipes', 'Which of the following is NOT a traditional ingredient in Caesar salad dressing?', 'Anchovies', 'Cream', 'Garlic', 'Olive Oil', 'B', NULL),
        (50, 'Recipes', 'What is the main ingredient in chicken Kiev (other than the chicken)?', 'Butter', 'Cheese', 'Ham', 'Spinach', 'A', 'Chicken Kiev is a chicken breast containing herbed chilled butter dipped in egg and breadcrumbs, then fried. '),
        (50, 'Recipes', 'Confit is a preparation usually made with which of the following?', 'Duck', 'Pork', 'Rabbit', 'Salmon', 'A', 'The duck is cooked and preserved in its own fat. '),
        (50, 'Recipes', 'Which of the following vegetables is used in Du Barry preparations?', 'Carrot', 'Cauliflower', 'Endive', 'White Asparagus', 'B', 'Du Barry refers to several dishes that contain cauliflower. These dishes were dedicated to the Comtesse du Barry, the favorite of the French King Louis XV.'),
        (50, 'Recipes', 'Duxelles is a cooked mixture of finely chopped shallots and which of the following?', 'Carrots', 'Celery', 'Green Peppers', 'Mushrooms', 'D', 'The ingredients are cooked in butter, and the preparation is used as a garnish or to flavor sauces and soups. '),
        (50, 'Recipes', 'Falafel is made with which of the following?', 'Chickpeas', 'Eggplant', 'Lamb', 'Pistachios', 'A', 'Falafel consists of deep fried balls of spiced ground chickpeas, served in a pita bread with a yogurt or tahini-based sauce. '),
        (50, 'Recipes', 'The term "Florentine" indicates the use of which vegetable?', 'Arugula', 'Broccoli', 'Onions', 'Spinach', 'D', 'Florentine dishes also usually contain eggs or fish and Mornay sauce. '),
        (50, 'Recipes', 'What country is gado gado from?', 'Hawaii', 'Indonesia', 'The Philippines', 'Sri Lanka', 'B', 'Gado gado is a vegetable concoction that is served with a spicy peanut sauce. '),
        (50, 'Recipes', 'In French, a grenouille is', 'A Small Wild Bird', 'Calf\'S Brain', 'Chicken Gizzards', 'A Frog', 'D', NULL),
        (50, 'Recipes', 'Which of the following is the main ingredient in guacamole?', 'Avocado', 'Eggplant', 'Garlic', 'Green Pepper', 'A', 'Guacamole consists of avocadoes mixed with lemon or lime juice, red pepper, chopped tomato, green onion, cilantro and sometimes chili powder. '),
        (50, 'Recipes', 'What kind of meat is used in hasenpfeffer?', 'Beef', 'Pork', 'Rabbit', 'Veal', 'C', 'Hasenpfeffer is usually served with sour cream and noodles or dumplings. '),
        (50, 'Recipes', 'Kimchi is a dish from', 'Korea', 'Indonesia', 'Japan', 'Thailand', 'A', 'Kimchee is served with every meal in Korea. There are many varieties of kimchee but the most common North American version consists of fermented cabbage, garlic, sugar and spices.'),
        (50, 'Recipes', 'Thermidor is a name associated with', 'Crab', 'Lobster', 'Shrimp', 'Scallops', 'B', 'Lobster Thermidor is a mixture of cheese, lobster meat, egg yolks, and brandy or sherry, stuffed into a lobster shell and browned. It was created in 1894 at Marie\'s, a Paris restaurant, in honor of the opening of the play Thermidor.'),
        (50, 'Recipes', 'In what country would you find masa harina?', 'India', 'Indonesia', 'Madagascar', 'Mexico', 'D', 'Masa harina is the dough ("masa") that is used to make corn tortillas. "Harina" is the Spanish word for "flour.'),
        (50, 'Recipes', 'Moussaka is a Greek dish traditionally made with lamb and', 'Avocado', 'Beans', 'Eggplant', 'Olives', 'C', 'This layered casserole also contains béchamel sauce, cheese, tomatoes and onions. '),
        (50, 'Recipes', 'Muffuletta is the name of a type of', 'Olive Salad', 'Salami', 'Sandwich', 'Tomato', 'C', 'A muffuletta consists of crusty Italian bread filled with Italian cold cuts, cheese, olives, red bell pepper and a garlic mixture. '),
        (50, 'Recipes', 'A salad of tomatoes, hard-cooked egg, radish, olives, tuna, potatoes, green beans and sometimes anchovies is called', 'Chef', 'Cobb', 'Niçoise', 'Waldorf', 'C', 'Salade Niçoise is a specialty of the Côte D\'Azur region of France; it originated in and is named for the city of Nice. '),
        (50, 'Recipes', 'Potatoes O\'Brien is an Irish dish prepared with onions and', 'Cheese', 'Cream', 'Peppers', 'Tomatoes', 'C', 'The potatoes and pepper are fried together in butter and served hot. '),
        (50, 'Recipes', 'Panna cotta is an Italian', 'Cooking Utensil', 'Dessert', 'Fried Cheese', 'Meat Dish', 'B', 'Panna cotta is made by simmering cream, milk and sugar, adding gelatin and allowing the dish to cool and set. The Italian name literally means "cooked cream.'),
        (50, 'Recipes', 'Which of the following herbs is used in pesto?', 'Basil', 'Oregano', 'Parsley', 'Tarragon', 'A', 'Pesto is an uncooked sauce that contains basil, garlic, olive oil, Parmigiano or Pecorino cheese and, occasionally, pine nuts. '),
        (50, 'Recipes', 'Risotto Milanese is a rice dish that contains which spice?', 'Cumin', 'Nutmeg', 'Paprika', 'Saffron', 'D', NULL),
        (50, 'Recipes', 'Which of the following is the main ingredient of the Greek dish saganaki?', 'Cheese', 'Egg', 'Lamb', 'Spinach', 'A', 'Kasseri is one of the traditional cheeses used to make saganaki, which consists of a slice of cheese fried in olive oil, sometimes flambéed with brandy or Ouzo, and sprinkled with lemon juice. '),
        (50, 'Recipes', 'Scotch woodcock is made with which of the following?', 'Anchovies', 'Woodcock', 'Scotch', 'Scotch And Woodcock', 'A', 'Scotch woodcock contains neither Scotch nor woodcock. Instead, it is toast topped with anchovy paste or fillets and scrambled eggs.'),
        (50, 'Recipes', 'What is spanakopita?', 'Fried Cheese', 'Lamb Kebab', 'Savory Pie', 'Sweet Flaky Dessert', 'C', 'Spanakopita consists of spinach, onions, feta cheese, eggs and seasonings with a filo dough crust. '),
        (50, 'Recipes', 'Which of the following is one of the traditional ingredients of succotash?', 'Green Beans', 'Green Peppers', 'Kidney Beans', 'Lima Beans', 'D', 'Succotash is a bean and corn dish from the southern USA. '),
        (50, 'Recipes', 'Tabbouleh is made with which of the following?', 'Lamb', 'Oranges', 'Pistachios', 'Wheat', 'D', 'This Middle Eastern dish is made from bulgur wheat, chopped tomatoes, onions, parsley, mint, lemon juice and olive oil. '),
        (50, 'Recipes', 'What is tahini made from?', 'Chickpeas', 'Lemons', 'Ripe Olives', 'Sesame Seeds', 'D', 'Tahini is a thick paste of ground sesame seeds used as a flavoring in many Middle Eastern dishes. '),
        (50, 'Recipes', 'Tapenade is a thick paste made from lemon juice, olive oil, olives, anchovies and which of the following?', 'Capers', 'Garlic', 'Green Peppers', 'Onions', 'A', 'Tapenade is served with crudités, used as a condiment and served with grilled fish and meat. The word is from the Provençal "tapeno," which means "caper.'),
        (50, 'Recipes', 'Waldorf salad does NOT contain which of the following?', 'Apples', 'Celery', 'Croutons', 'Walnuts', 'C', 'A Waldorf salad contains diced apple, celery (or celeriac), walnuts and mayonnaise. It is named after the famous New York City Hotel, the Waldorf Astoria.'),
        (50, 'Sauce', 'Albuféra sauce is made with', 'Beets', 'Bell Peppers', 'Cauliflower', 'Mushrooms', 'B', 'Puréed red bell peppers give Albuféra sauce a pink color; chili pepper and saffron add flavor. '),
        (50, 'Sauce', 'In addition to mayonnaise, pimento and lemon juice, what else is in Andalouse sauce?', 'Anchovies', 'Avocado', 'Spinach', 'Tomato Paste', 'D', 'Andalouse sauce goes very well with french fries and with large cuts of meat. Paprika, parsley, garlic and Worcestershire sauce are also sometimes added.'),
        (50, 'Sauce', 'Which of the following is used to flavor béarnaise sauce?', 'Cilantro', 'Parsley', 'Tarragon', 'Thyme', 'C', 'Béarnaise sauce is made with vinegar, shallots, wine, egg yolks and butter, and flavored with tarragon. '),
        (50, 'Sauce', 'Which of the following is frequently used to flavor béchamel sauce?', 'Cinnamon', 'Mustard Seed', 'Nutmeg', 'Oregano', 'C', NULL),
        (50, 'Sauce', 'Which of the following is NOT an emulsified sauce?', 'Béarnaise', 'Béchamel', 'Hollandaise', 'Paprika', 'B', 'Emulsified sauces are made of a combination of two liquids that do not ordinarily combine smoothly into a uniform mixture. '),
        (50, 'Sauce', 'Genevoise is a classic sauce served with', 'Ham', 'Fish', 'Lamb', 'Poultry', 'B', 'Genevoise consists of a mirepoix and brown sauce with red wine, fish fumet, anchovy paste and mushrooms. '),
        (50, 'Sauce', 'What is harissa?', 'A Condiment', 'Soup', 'Stew', 'A Type Of Bean', 'A', 'This North African and Middle Eastern condiment is a purée of hot chili peppers, garlic, cumin and other spices and herbs; it is used as an accompaniment to couscous as well as to other dishes. '),
        (50, 'Sauce', 'In Cantonese, the sauce known as Hoisin means', 'Seafood', 'Southern', 'Sticky', 'Sweet Black', 'A', 'Hoisin sauce is made from soya beans, vinegar, sugar, garlic and spices. Even though its name means "seafood" it does not contain seafood.'),
        (50, 'Sauce', 'In what country did Hollandaise sauce originate?', 'Belgium', 'France', 'Great Britain', 'Holland', 'D', 'Hollandaise is a hot emulsified sauce based on egg yolks and clarified butter. '),
        (50, 'Sauce', 'A maltaise is a hollandaise sauce that includes which of the following?', 'Brandy', 'Chicken Stock', 'Ham', 'Orange', 'D', 'A maltaise is a sweet or savory sauce based on oranges, particularly the Maltese blood orange. It is excellent with asparagus and green beans.'),
        (50, 'Sauce', 'What fruit is Melba sauce made with?', 'Blueberries', 'Cherries', 'Raspberries', 'Apricots', 'C', 'Red currants (in jelly form) are also used. '),
        (50, 'Sauce', 'Which of the following sauces contains cheese?', 'Béarnaise', 'Béchamel', 'Mornay', 'Véronique', 'C', 'Mornay sauce is a béchamel sauce with the addition of Gruyère or Parmigiano cheese. '),
        (50, 'Sauce', 'Newburg sauce is composed of butter, cream, egg yolks and which of the following?', 'Brandy', 'Pernod', 'Sherry', 'White Wine', 'C', 'Newburg sauce is usually served with cooked shellfish. '),
        (50, 'Sauce', 'Piri-piri is a', 'Chili Sauce', 'Fish Soup', 'Salt Water Fish', 'Spicy Tomato Sauce', 'A', 'Piri-piri originated in Portugal. '),
        (50, 'Sauce', 'Soubise is a rich white sauce made with', 'Celery', 'Garlic', 'Leeks', 'Onions', 'D', 'Cream is sometimes also added. The sauce is named for an 18th century French aristocrat, Charles de Rohan, Prince of Soubise.'),
        (50, 'Sauce', 'Tamari is similar to which of the following?', 'Corn Starch', 'Horseradish', 'Meat Pâté', 'Soy Sauce', 'D', 'The Japanese sauce known as tamari is thicker than soy sauce and is used as a dipping sauce or for basting. '),
        (50, 'Science', 'Which of the following is NOT among the eight foods that cause 90 per cent of allergic reactions?', 'Eggs', 'Milk', 'Sesame Seeds', 'Tomatoes', 'D', 'The eight foods that cause 90 per cent of allergic reactions are eggs, milk, sesame seeds, peanuts, tree nuts, wheat, soy and sulfites. '),
        (50, 'Science', 'What percentage of American adults have food allergies?', '3 To 4 Per Cent', '5 To 6 Per Cent', '7 To 8 Per Cent', '9 To 10 Per Cent', 'A', NULL),
        (50, 'Science', 'Which of the following can inhibit the absorption of some prescription drugs?', 'Coffee', 'Grapefruit', 'Honey', 'Peanuts', 'B', NULL),
        (50, 'Science', 'The tip of the tongue detects which of the following most effectively?', 'Bitter', 'Salty', 'Sour', 'Sweet', 'D', NULL),
        (50, 'Seafood', 'Anchovy is a type of which of the following?', 'Fish', 'Preserved Egg', 'Spice', 'Vegetable', 'A', 'The anchovy is a small sea fish that is rarely sold fresh. Instead, anchovies are usually sold salted and in jars, as whole fish in oil or as fillets in cans.'),
        (50, 'Seafood', 'In Portugal, what is dried and salted codfish called?', 'Bacalhau', 'Pico', 'Rabacai', 'Saloio', 'A', 'It is claimed that there are more than 365 ways to cook bacalhau. Pico, Rabacai and Saloio are all Portuguese cheeses.'),
        (50, 'Seafood', 'Which of the following was served in American saloons in the 19th century to encourage drinking?', 'Beef Jerky', 'Caviar', 'Cheese Curds', 'Soya Nuts', 'B', 'At the beginning of the 19th century, the US was the major producer of caviar. '),
        (50, 'seafood', 'Which is the least desirable type of salmon?', 'Chinook', 'Chum', 'Coho', 'Sockeye', 'B', 'Chum has the lowest oil content of all salmons and is consequently less flavorful. '),
        (50, 'Seafood', 'What is cobia?', 'Fish', 'Fruit', 'Sheep', 'Tuber', 'A', 'Also known as black king fish or black salmon, cobia are warm water fish that resemble mackerel; they have a firm texture and excellent flavor. '),
        (50, 'Seafood', 'The most widely eaten fish in the world is', 'Cod ', 'Herring', 'Salmon', 'Tuna', 'B', 'There are fifteen species of this small oily fish, which is found mainly in the cold waters of the North Atlantic and the North Sea. '),
        (50, 'Seafood', 'Matelote is a', 'Fish Stew', 'Fruit Tarte', 'Large Beer Glass', 'Thin Knife For Filleting', 'A', 'This highly seasoned stew is made with freshwater fish, wine and stock. "Matelot" is French for "sailor.'),
        (50, 'Seafood', 'Monkfish has lean, flavorful white flesh that is often compared to which of the following?', 'Cod', 'Crab', 'Lobster', 'Tuna', 'C', 'The only edible part of the monkfish is the tail. Monkfish can be sustituted for lobster in most dishes.'),
        (50, 'Seafood', 'Which state produces nearly half of the US total oyster harvest?', 'Louisiana', 'Maine', 'Texas', 'Washington', 'A', 'More than 130,000 tons of live oysters are harvested in the US every year. '),
        (50, 'Seafood', 'Which of the following is the most popular seafood in America?', 'Salmon', 'Shrimp', 'Sole', 'Tuna', 'B', 'This small shellfish pushed tuna out of the top spot in 2001. '),
        (50, 'soup', 'Menudo refers to a Mexican', 'Fish Fritter', 'Fried Pastry', 'Spicy Soup', 'Tequila-Based Cocktail', 'C', 'Menudo is made with tripe and eaten with corn tortillas. '),
        (50, 'Soup', 'The essential vegetable in Potage Saint-Germain is', 'Beans', 'Green Peppers', 'Peas', 'Spinach', 'C', 'Potage Saint-Germain is a thick green pea soup enriched with butter. '),
        (50, 'Soup', 'Scotch broth is made with vegetables, barley and which of the following?', 'Beef', 'Lamb', 'Pork', 'Woodcock', 'B', 'Mutton is also used. '),
        (50, 'soup', 'What are you eating if you are eating terrapin?', 'Crab', 'Eel', 'Scallop', 'Turtle', 'D', 'But you shouldn\'t be eating it. In the US only farm-raised freshwater turtles and a few wild turtles can legally be eaten. The diamondback terrapin is protected by law along the entire eastern seaboard. '),
        (50, 'Spirits', 'Which of the following is NOT a fortified wine?', 'Armagnac', 'Port', 'Sherry', 'Vermouth', 'A', 'Armagnac is a type of brandy from southwestern France. '),
        (50, 'Spirits', 'Where does the alcoholic beverage cachaça come from?', 'Argentina', 'Brazil', 'Mexico', 'Portugal', 'B', 'Cachaça is distilled from sugar cane. '),
        (50, 'Spirits', 'Calvados is a brandy derived from which fruit?', 'Apple', 'Lemon', 'Orangepear', 'Orange', 'A', 'Calvados is made in Calvados, in the Normandy region of France. '),
        (50, 'Spirits', 'Which of the following is NOT an anise-flavored liqueur?', 'Chartreuse', 'Ouzo', 'Pastis', 'Pernod', 'A', 'Although 130 plants go into making Chartreuse, among them angelica, cinnamon bark, mace and saffron, Chartreuse is not known as an anise-flavored liqueur. '),
        (50, 'Spirits', 'Demerara rum is made from sugar cane grown along the banks of the Demerara river in which Caribbean country?', 'Jamaica', 'Guyana', 'Puerto Rico', 'Trinidad', 'B', NULL),
        (50, 'Spirits', 'In what country was gin developed?', 'Belgium', 'England', 'Holland', 'India', 'C', 'A 17th century professor of medicine mixed grain spirit with juniper-berry extract to create gin. '),
        (50, 'Spirits', 'The country with the highest per capita consumption of gin is', 'Britain', 'Germany', 'Holland', 'Spain', 'D', 'However, the USA is the world\'s largest market for gin. '),
        (50, 'Spirits', 'Which of the following is a single malt Scotch?', 'Cutty Sark', 'Dewar\'S', 'Glenfiddich', 'Johnnie Walker', 'C', NULL),
        (50, 'Spirits', 'Which of the following is NOT considered one of the three great French brandies?', 'Armagnac', 'Calvados', 'Cognac', 'Grand Marnier', 'D', 'This orange-flavored beverage is a liqueur not a brandy. '),
        (50, 'Spirits', 'What is grappa?', 'A Box For Transporting Grapes', 'A Distilled Beverage From Italy', 'A Grape Juice', 'A Soda Pop', 'B', 'Grappa is distilled from the grape seeds, stalks and stems discarded during wine making. '),
        (50, 'Spirits', 'Which of the following is an Irish whiskey?', 'Glenlivet', 'Jameson', 'Jim Beam', 'Johnnie Walker', 'B', 'This is a blended whiskey, made by Midleton Distillery, one of only three distilleries making Irish whiskey. '),
        (50, 'Spirits', 'What is Okolehao?', 'A Liqueur', 'A Pineapple Soda', 'A Pork Dish', 'A Tea-Based Beverage', 'A', 'This Hawaiian liqueur is made from the root of the ti plant (a member of the agave family) and is about 80 proof (40 per cent alcohol). '),
        (50, 'Spirits', 'Prior to Prohibition, what was the most popular type of whiskey in America?', 'Bourbon', 'Malt', 'Rye', 'Vodka', 'C', 'After Prohibition rye was replaced by bourbon. '),
        (50, 'Spirits', 'Sabra liqueur is made in', 'Brazil', 'Greece', 'Israel', 'Portugal', 'C', 'Sabra\'s main flavor is bittersweet chocolate, which is cut by the sweet and sour taste of jaffa oranges. '),
        (50, 'Spirits', 'What grain is the basis of single malt Scotch?', 'Barley', 'Corn', 'Rye', 'Wheat', 'A', 'The recipe for Scotch whiskey, the national drink of Scotland, has changed little over hundreds of years. The first step is to dry malted barley over peat fires, which imparts a particular flavor to the whiskey.'),
        (50, 'Spirits', 'Slivovitz is a brandy made from', 'Apples', 'Cherries', 'Pears', 'Plums', 'D', 'The national drink of the Bosnians and Serbs, slivovitz is a true alcohol, not just brandy flavored with fruit. '),
        (50, 'Spirits', 'Southern Comfort is an American liqueur made from bourbon and which of the following?', 'Apple', 'Apricot', 'Orange', 'Peach', 'D', 'Southern Comfort was first created in 1875 and was known as Cuff and Buttons. A bartender in St. Louis, Missouri, changed its name to Southern Comfort. '),
        (50, 'Spirits', 'In what century was whiskey was first made in the US?', '16Th', '17Th', '18Th', '19Th', 'B', 'It was made from a mixture of corn and rye. '),
        (50, 'Statistics', 'What is the favorite dish of most Argentinians?', 'Chicken Kebab', 'Shrimp', 'Spiced Pork', 'Steak', 'D', 'With its vast grazing lands, Argentina produces a large quantity of beef, which is a principal diet staple. '),
        (50, 'Statistics', 'What country consumes the most beer per capita?', 'Czech Republic', 'Germany', 'Ireland', 'Usa', 'A', NULL),
        (50, 'Statistics', 'In 2005, Americans spent what percentage of their food dollars eating out?', '23', '35', '47', '55', 'C', NULL),
        (50, 'Statistics', 'Americans eat approximately what percentage of their meals away from home each year?', '20', '30', '40', '50', 'A', NULL),
        (50, 'Statistics', 'In which country do people eat the least often at sit-down restaurants?', 'France', 'Germany', 'Italy', 'Russia', 'D', NULL),
        (50, 'Statistics', 'What percentage of Americans had their first job in a restaurant?', '10', '15', '20', '32', 'D', NULL),
